UT/CSR monthly 5x5 gravity harmonics
 
This file contains monthly estimates of the time-variable geopotential up
to degree and order 5 (+C61/S61) determined from satellite laser ranging from
five geodetic satellites spanning January 2002 to present .
 
The coefficients are given as variations relative to the mean gravity field
GGM05C, which are provided in this file. All coefficients are normalized.
The variations should be added to GGM05C to obtain the full coefficient.
 
The estimates are provided without and with the RL06 Atmosphere-Ocean 
De-aliasing (AOD) model restored (the AOD was included 
during processing). The estimates with AOD restored should be added to 
GGM05C to obtain the full signal.
 
For a reference, please use: Cheng, M., J. C.  Ries, and B. D. Tapley (2011)
Variations of the Earth's Figure Axis from Satellite Laser Ranging and GRACE,
J. Geophys. Res., 116, B01409, 2011, DOI:10.1029/2010JB000850.

PLEASE NOTE: There are several changes with respect to the previously 
delivered product and with respect to the above reference. The estimation
strategy is largely the same except for these differences:

1) Degree-1 will not be included here but will be provided in
a separate degree-1 product based exclusively on LAGEOS-1 and 2. 

2) The LARES satellite is included when it is available in early 2012. This
leads to considerable improvement in the recover of the odd zonals.

3) Forward-models for the higher-degree terms to degree/order 60 are 
used based on GRACE and GRACE-FO. This significantly improves the
recovery of C30 and should improve the estimates for other harmonics
as well, particularly C20.
